title: [feature-wip](multi-catalog) lazy read for ParquetReader
body:
# Proposed changes

Support lazy read for non-predicate columns in `ParquetReader`.

## Method
Read predicate columns firstly, and use `VExprContext`(push-down predicates) to generate the select vector, which is then applied to read the non-predicate columns.
The data in non-predicate columns may be skipped by select vector, so the value-decode-time can be reduced. If a whole page can be skipped, the decompress-time  can also be reduced.

## Performance Test
Using one thread to query data in table with 10 million rows, and the table is generated from a [data generator tool](https://github.com/glebkorolkov/datagen) with all types supported by hive, and all values are random, and has a 10% probability of being null.
1. No performance fallback in the worst case(filter_ration=10%, 50%)
2. When filter_ration > 90%, the performance is more than doubled.
![4INIM2Hwkh](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/19337507/200860805-5d00fad5-dd09-4c36-8432-902947f19fcf.jpg)

## Remaining Problems
1. Predicates with partition columns can't trigger lazy read. Support in later PR.
2. Can't apply the later arrived runtime filters to lazy read.
3. Even if a page can be skipped, the data in this page may be read (not decompressed) for [pre-reading](https://github.com/apache/doris/pull/12898).

title: [enhancement](Nereids) add eliminate unnecessary project rule
body:
# Proposed changes

This rule eliminate project that output set is same with its child. If the project is the root of plan, the elimination condition is project's output is exactly the same with its child.

The reason to add this rule is when we do join reorder in optimization, the root of plan after transformed maybe a Project and its output set is same with the root of plan before transformed. If we had a Project on the top of the root and its output set is same with the root of plan too. We will have two exactly same projects in memo. One of them is the parent of the other. After MergeProject, we will get a new Project exactly same like the child and need to add to parent's group. Then we trigger Merge Group. Since merge will produce a cycle, the merge will be denied and we will get a final plan with two consecutive projects.

## for example:
**BEFORE OPTIMIZATION**
```
LogicalProject1( projects=[c_custkey#0, c_name#1]) [GroupId#1]
+--LogicalJoin(type=LEFT_SEMI_JOIN)                [GroupId#2]
   |--LogicalProject(...)
   |  +--LogicalJoin(type=INNER_JOIN)
   |  ...
   +--LogicalOlapScan(...)
```
**AFTER APPLY RULE: LOGICAL_SEMI_JOIN_LOGICAL_JOIN_TRANSPOSE_PROJECT**
```
LogicalProject1( projects=[c_custkey#0, c_name#1])    [GroupId#1]
+--LogicalProject2( projects=[c_custkey#0, c_name#1]) [GroupId#2]
   +--LogicalJoin(type=INNER_JOIN)                    [GroupId#10]
      |--LogicalProject(...)
      |  +--LogicalJoin(type=LEFT_SEMI_JOIN)
      |  ...
      +--LogicalOlapScan(...)
```
**AFTER APPLY RULE: MERGE_PROJECTS**
```
LogicalProject3( projects=[c_custkey#0, c_name#1])  [should be in GroupId#1, but in GroupId#2 in fact]
+--LogicalJoin(type=INNER_JOIN)                     [GroupId#10]
   |--LogicalProject(...)
   |  +--LogicalJoin(type=LEFT_SEMI_JOIN)
   |  ...
   +--LogicalOlapScan(...)
```
Since we have exaclty GroupExpression(LogicalProject3 and LogicalProject2) in GroupId#1 and GroupId#2, we need to do MergeGroup(GroupId#1, GroupId#2). But we have child of GroupId#1 in GroupId#2. So the merge is denied.
If the best GroupExpression in GroupId#2 is LogicalProject3, we will get two consecutive projects in the final plan.

# Proposed changes

Issue Number: close #xxx

## Problem summary

1.
Support running transactional insert operation with new scan framework. eg:
```
admin set frontend config("enable_new_load_scan_node" = "true");
begin;
insert into tbl1 values(1,2);
insert into tbl1 values(3,4);
insert into tbl1 values(5,6);
commit;
```

2. Add some limitation to transactional insert
    1. Do not support non-literal value in insert stmt

3. Fix some issue about array type:
    1. Forbid cast other non-array type to NESTED array type, it may cause BE crash.
    2. Add `getStringValueForArray()` method for Expr, to get valid string-formatted array type value.

title: [enhancement](memtracker) Refactor load channel + memtable mem tracker
body:
# Proposed changes

Issue Number: close #xxx

## Problem summary

In the load test, the problem is analyzed according to the mem tracker, and it is found that:
1. In the memtable insert stage, the memory recorded by the mem hook is less than that recorded manually, and the value recorded manually is closer to the real value.
2. The memory value recorded by the mem hook is relatively accurate during the memtable flushing stage.
3. The current mem tracker recording method has a high understanding threshold and is not easy to analyze.

For 3.
- When the memory value of the mem table is greater than `config::write_buffer_size (default 200M), flush it, which depends on manually recording the memory;
- `LoadChannelMgr` checks the total memory of all load channels before each add batch. If it exceeds the limit, select the load channel to flush, which relies on mem hook to record memory;
It is not easy to understand that two different memory recording methods are mixed;

So, I simplified the use of mem tracker, looking forward to better understanding.
